text.tspan: Child mortality: IHME vs UN IGME estimates, 2017
Child mortality is the share of newborns who die before reaching the age of five. This compares estimates from the
IHME, Global Burden of Disease study and the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (IGME).
Source: IHME; UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation
